      "content": "Given that the H100 nodes are being decommissioned entirely, the optimization plan needs to be adjusted to focus on minimizing the impact on running jobs and ensuring a smooth transition to the remaining hardware.\n\nFirst, prioritize the jobs that are currently running on the H100 nodes and identify the ones that are most critical to the overall workflow. These jobs should be given the highest priority to complete before the H100 nodes are taken offline.\n\nNext, consider migrating these critical jobs to the remaining H100 nodes or to other available nodes that can handle the workload. If possible, use job queuing and checkpointing to ensure that jobs can be restarted from the last checkpoint if they get killed due to resource constraints.\n\nSince the H100 nodes are being decommissioned, it's unlikely that you can migrate jobs to these nodes. Instead, focus on optimizing the workflow to minimize the impact of the H100 nodes being taken offline. This might involve:\n\n* Canceling or pausing non-essential jobs that are running on the H100 nodes\n* Migrating non-critical jobs to other nodes or to a different time slot\n* Using load balancing and resource allocation strategies to distribute the workload across the remaining nodes\n* Implementing a \"job graveyard\" strategy,",
